Six million Jewish men, women, and children were murdered by the Nazi regime. Let us never forget the suffering endured and lives lost, and let us always remember the example of the survivors’ strength. Today, we honor their memory.  #YomHaShoah

The steep rise in anti-Semitism cannot be tolerated. This year, more than in recent years, we must thoughtfully commemorate Yom HaShoah. Less than a century ago, hatred and evil forced an attempted eradication of an entire population of people – our Jewish brothers and sisters.

On this day…1943 - Jews in the Warsaw ghetto fought back against Nazi officials who would have deported them to killing centers. The resisters held out for nearly a month. Today, #WeRemember their bravery and courage. We can never again tolerate anti-Semitism.
